title: Drive in the EU after Brexit: lorry and goods vehicle drivers
withdrawn_explanation:
This page is out of date. It told you how to prepare for a no-deal Brexit.

After 31 January 2020 there will be a transition period until the end of 2020, while the UK and EU negotiate additional arrangements.

The current rules for international lorry and goods vehicle drivers will continue to apply during the transition period.

The British Embassy in Pyongyang temporarily closed in May 2020 due to travel restrictions put in place by the DPRK Government in response to the COVID-19 pandemic and is currently unable to provide any consular assistance. You can contact the Foreign, Commonwealth & Development Office on +44 (0)20 7008 1500, if you require any urgent consular assistance.

British Nationals thinking of travelling to North Korea should regularly check the Foreign, Commonwealth & Development Offices travel advice for North Korea.
